Thank you for helping stop a $50 million cut to Great Lakes!  We need you to keep up the fight – POTUS said he wants to zero out next year's funds!
Every week when Congress is in session, I invite constituents who are in DC from across our state to Good Morning Michigan!  We had a great group of folks last week. Thanks for joining!
#TBT to being the first woman to preside over the Michigan State House. I've always been committed to fighting for families, growing our economy and protecting our Michigan way of life.

We need to be laser focused on creating jobs right here in Michigan.  My American Jobs Agenda continues my commitment to making products in this country, closing loopholes that hurt workers and businesses, and holding countries like China accountable for unfair trade practices.  I applaud great businesses like Detroit Denim Co. and Rogers Foam who are committed to investing in our workers!
#TBT I have always loved music.  It’s one of the best ways for me to unwind when things get stressful.  I'm playing the piano a lot these days!!
Thankful the U.S. Navy has made sure Machinist Mate First Class Fred M. Jones will return to his final resting place in Port Huron.
Tune in to my page today at 2:30pm to watch! #AmericaSpeaksOut on #Trumpcare
It is deeply troubling that President Trump fired FBI Director Comey, who was leading the Trump-Russia investigation. We need an independent prosecutor!
Tune in! U.S. Senate Democrats are hearing from people across the country who would be hurt by #Trumpcare.  Be sure to share your story using the hashtag #AmericaSpeaksOut!
Thank you, Rod Nelson, CEO of #Mackinac Straits Health System, for explaining how the Republican health care plan would hurt rural communities in Michigan.
Honored to receive this recognition from Gary Kushner and the Small Business Council of America

I just had the pleasure of meeting with Oakridge High School students who came all the way from Muskegon to deliver a stack of petitions in support of AmeriCorps and its critical work. Thank you to the 1,400 AmeriCorps members in Michigan who dedicate their time and skills to over 70 local projects that make a huge difference in our communities. I will continue to fight for the funding that AmeriCorps needs to make sure these wonderful volunteers can serve our country.

We need a special prosecutor to look into potential ties between President Trump and Russia.  This is not a partisan issue or a Republican or Democratic issue; it is about the security of the United States and protecting our country from a foreign government that is not our friend.

Moms and families in Michigan depend on access to quality, affordable health care, including maternity coverage.  Today, I joined Patty Murray, Kirsten Gillibrand, Senator Maggie Hassan and the author of What To Expect to oppose the House Republican health care plan.  It basically imposes a pregnancy tax on women. That makes no sense!
Come on down for the grand opening of the QLINE!
Riding the QLINE with Rep. Brenda Lawrence!

The new QLINE streetcar system is the next step in connecting people to wonderful destinations in Detroit while supporting local businesses and jobs. It’s very exciting to welcome this new motor to the Motor City!
Glad to be back at the Komen Detroit Race for the Cure® this morning with all of the courageous women, families, and friends. Together, we'll find a cure for cancer.
Happy Mother's Day to you! Celebrating my wonderful mother, Ann Greer, today and every day and Michelle and Sara, the beautiful mothers of my grandchildren!

For over a year, I have been doing a small business tour across Michigan and have visited 86 great businesses so far! I have met with folks in Fenton, St. Ignace, Bay City, Battle Creek, St. Johns, Onaway, South Haven, Utica, Three Rivers and so many more cities and towns in our great state. Thank you for all you do, small business owners!

ICYMI: Read my Lansing State Journal op-ed on how the Farm Bill strengthens Michigan's food and agriculture industry, which supports 1 in 4 jobs across our state. As we begin work on the 2018 Farm Bill, I will ensure that Michigan has a strong voice in the process from start to finish.

Earlier this month, Senate Ag Committee Chairman Pat Roberts and I held a field hearing on the 2018 Farm Bill in Frankenmuth, Michigan where we heard from food and agricultural leaders from all over our state. In the 2014 Farm Bill, I made sure Michigan was on every page and I will continue to ensure that our state is represented in the process. Together, we will continue the tradition of working to support our jobs, farmers and families!

Families in Michigan are losing too many loved ones to drug addiction.  That’s why I have worked hard to increase funding for treatment services.  While we have a lot more work to do, there is some good news.    Read my column in The Mining Journal to learn more:

Last week, I chaired a hearing featuring people from across the country who would be hurt by the Republican health care plan, which dramatically increases costs for families while taking away health care for tens of millions of Americans. All to pay for a tax cut for millionaires and billionaires. This is stunningly irresponsible!
Great to meet so many talented young people who are part of University of Michigan's Carson Scholars program!
Stunning news of how President Trump tried to influence the FBI’s Russia investigation.  We need answers and an independent special prosecutor.

National Police Week is a time to honor the courageous men and women who risk everything in order to protect our communities. Remembering the sacrifice and service of all who serve and those who have fallen.

I welcome the important news that the Justice Department has appointed a special counsel to look into ties between President Trump’s campaign and Russia.  Former FBI Director Robert Mueller is a highly qualified and well-respected law enforcement official who served both Presidents Bush and Obama.  I encourage him to move quickly to examine the facts and conduct a thorough investigation.  The American people deserve answers so we can move forward and focus on jobs and the other critical challenges facing our families and communities.

This #WomensHealthWeek, it is more important than ever for us to stand together to protect women’s access to basic health care. We must work to ensure quality care and lower costs for women and their families in Michigan.

Honoring and thanking the brave men and women in our military on this Armed Forces Day. U.S. Army, U.S. Marine Corps, U.S. Navy, U.S. Air Force and U.S. Coast Guard, you courageously serve and protect our home. You make our freedom possible.
President Trump's budget just came out. Terrible news for the Great Lakes! We need you to speak out and get involved!

Parents’ worst fears were realized today when Secretary DeVos outlined the Trump Administration’s plan to shift billions of dollars away from our nation’s public schools. These policies have already failed children and families in Michigan. Instead, we should be working cooperatively to improve our schools, not playing politics with the future of our children.

I have heard too many stories of lives lost due to opioid overdose. Drug abuse has increased dramatically nationwide, and here in Michigan, the drug overdose death rate is above the national average. I just spoke with WLNS-TV about what Congress is going to do to tackle this epidemic.

This non-partisan #CBO report confirms once again that Trumpcare is a bad deal for Michigan families.  It raises costs and takes us back to the days when insurance companies were in charge of your health care. If you or your family member has a “preexisting condition” like cancer, pregnancy, or diabetes, you could lose coverage or be forced to pay a lot more.  I’m ready to work across the aisle to lower costs and improve care for Michigan families, but this plan makes people pay more for less

In the Budget Committee Hearing today, I asked OMB Director Mulvaney why the Trump budget fails to protect our Great Lakes. He doesn’t understand how important the Great Lakes are to our economy and to our Michigan way of life. This is completely unacceptable!
Ramadan Mubarak to all of my Muslims friends! Wishing you, your family and your community a blessed holy month filled with happiness and joy.
Thank you, Dr. Anthony Weinert - Stop Feet Pain Fast, for caring about our veterans! So important! So inspirational!
St. Clair Shores Memorial Day parade was awesome as usual!
Great to be part of honoring our fallen heroes in Dearborn today. Beautiful tribute!
I was honored to be part of Monroe's Memorial Day program including laying wreaths at the River Raisin National Battlefield Park.
Thousands of people have written to me demanding that we protect our Great Lakes. The Trump Administration should make this a national priority!

Thunder Bay's "Shipwreck Alley" is one of our great underwater treasures, attracting thousands of divers and visitors. Together, we can protect critical Great Lakes research funding that supports this National Marine Sanctuary!
Announcing New Legislation to Fund Soo Locks Upgrade
Senator Gary Peters and I are here on Mackinac Island to announce legislation to fund critical upgrades to the Soo Locks!

The Soo Locks are critical to our economy and our national security but they have not been upgraded in nearly 50 years.  Read my oped in Detroit Free Press about how the Michigan delegation is working together to secure full funding to update the Locks!

Did you know that the Soo Locks are our #1 infrastructure priority and are the gateway for iron ore, grain and materials that power our plants and make our products? I'm here today talking about why they need an upgrade! ‬
I sat down with WOOD TV8's Rick Albin to discuss exactly how the latest budget cuts would endanger our Great Lakes and hurt our way of life in Michigan.

Warmest congratulations to Claire Juip, from Grosse Pointe, on winning the The Library of Congress' Letters About Literature contest for her age group! At just nine years old, Claire and her optimism are an inspiration for us all.

I really enjoyed speaking with about 10,000 AARP Michigan members last night and meeting with Michigan AARP President Paula Cunningham today. One thing is clear: Trumpcare is a bad deal for Michigan seniors. Please continue to share your stories with me on my website and on Facebook so we can work together to improve health care for families and seniors in Michigan! https://www.stabenow.senate.gov/contact
Today I asked Secretary Tom Price why he thinks the cost of life saving drugs should be tens of thousands of dollars. He didn't have a good answer.
Wonderful start to the Detroit Music Weekend festival with the dedication of Aretha Franklin Way in Detroit! It's the perfect tribute to a great legend.

Great news today that Private First Class James McCloughan is finally getting the recognition he deserves for his service to our country!  I was honored to author legislation last year to make this possible and have Senator Gary Peters and Congressman Upton join me.
TUNE IN: Senate Democratic women are live on Facebook to talk about how disastrous Trumpcare would be for women and families.
My thoughts and prayers are with Congressman Steve Scalise, staffers, officers and first responders who were in this senseless and horrifying attack. Thank you for your bravery.

Mitch Albom’s personal story about Chika and her brave fight against brain cancer is truly incredible. I had the opportunity to meet Chika at the Faith Haiti Orphanage and her relationship with Mitch is a true love story.
NA
Sending warmest gratitude and respect to every man who is a dad, a papa, a grandpa or other loving role-model for our children. Happy Father’s Day!

This Juneteenth Independence Day let’s come together to celebrate priceless freedom and pay tribute to the historic end of slavery in Michigan and across our country. Today and every day, we need to recommit ourselves to the goal of equal opportunities for all Americans regardless of race or ethnicity.
NA
ICYMI: Last night, I spoke on the Senate floor to address GOP efforts to repeal health care behind closed doors. Republicans are hiding their bill because they know it’s bad for American families.

Republicans have a health care bill but they won’t let you see it.  The Trump Administration has seen it and K Street lobbyists have seen it but not the American people. If you have cancer and can’t get coverage or you’re a senior whose rates will skyrocket, you have a right to see this bill.  #SaveOurHealthCare #NoHearingNoVote
Watch live: U.S. Senate Democrats will hear from experts about how #Trumpcare will hurt rural communities.

It’s incredibly irresponsible for the Trump Administration to continue to block the Army Corps from releasing a crucial plan to address the threat of Asian carp to our Great Lakes! Our Great Lakes are so essential to our economy and our Michigan way of life. Today, Representative Marcy Kaptur (D-OH) and I introduced a bipartisan bill demanding the Trump Administration immediately release the report so we can move forward with a permanent solution to protect the Great Lakes from Asian carp.

For the people in Michigan who are purchasing on the private exchange -- over half are able to get a policy today for their families for less than $100 a month, for the 97% of children in Michigan who can now see a doctor, for the hospitals who are seeing 50% fewer people walking into the emergency room without insurance, for the $432 million in savings that the State of Michigan is going to have in its budget next year, this health care bill is wrong for Michigan!
Wishing my Muslim friends and communities in Michigan Eid Mubarak! May your celebrations be filled with lots of love, happiness and good food.

Once again, the nonpartisan CBO report shows that the Republican health care bill is a bad deal for Michigan families and for the country.  The Republican bill does nothing to address rising out-of-pocket and prescription drug costs.  Instead, it will raise costs for families, take away medical coverage, and use the savings to give a major tax cut to the wealthiest Americans.  And, buried in in the fine print, this bill will end the expanded Medicaid coverage that was used to help children and pregnant moms with lead exposure in Flint get comprehensive health care.  I urge my Senate Republican colleagues to vote "no" on proceeding to this bill, and instead, work with us to lower costs and improve health care for all Americans.

As I told Devin Scillian this weekend on WDIV Local 4 / ClickOnDetroit, health care is personal, not political. I want to work on improving health care for Michigan families by lowering prescription drug and out-of-pocket costs. Instead, Republicans want to pass a health care bill that increases costs and takes away care, all to give a tax cut to the wealthy.
Live now! I'm joining U.S. Senate Democrats, Senator Maggie Hassan, and prominent doctors' groups to talk about the harmful impacts of #Trumpcare.

Today I stood with doctors from across the country to share the stories of people who would be hurt by #Trumpcare.    We’re fighting for people like Amy, in Royal Oak, who needs cancer medication that costs $20,000 a month.  If we went back to the days when insurance companies were in charge and could impose lifetime limits on care, Amy could lose access to lifesaving treatment.    Thank you to all the doctors who came to DC to speak out!    American Academy of Family Physicians (AAFP) American College of Physicians American Psychiatric Association American Academy of Pediatrics The American Congress of Obstetricians and Gynecologists (ACOG National) Senator Maggie Hassan
3 out of 5 seniors in Michigan rely on Medicaid to get nursing home coverage. #Trumpcare threatens people like your parents or grandparents who need that care.

I spoke on the Senate Floor this week about the Republican health care bill and how it misses the mark for Michigan families and small businesses. Count me in if colleagues want to focus on improving health care and lowering out-of-pocket costs. But their bill takes away medical care and gives a tax cut to millionaires and billionaires. Watch here for more:

#Trumpcare hurts Michigan families, children, seniors, small business owners, pregnant moms, and more.  Thanks to WDIV Local 4 / ClickOnDetroit for a great explanation of what’s at stake over the next few weeks.
Adrian will always be a part of Team Stabenow.  I am excited to see him making a difference for the people of Flint!
Happy 4th of July to everyone in Michigan celebrating 241 years of our nation’s independence!
Great to celebrate our 4th of July at the Clawson Parade and a wonderful salute to veterans at the Clarkston-Independence Fest!

The sons of Kerri Causley and Marci West made the ultimate sacrifice defending our country’s independence. We owe these Gold Star mothers and all our Gold Star families in Michigan our deep gratitude.

Becoming the fastest growing economy in the U.S. is quite an accomplishment! Great to see our cities like Grand Rapids doing so well. Congrats to all the hard working people in Grand Rapids who make it such a great place to live and work.
With Rep Sandy Levin hearing healthcare stories from MI families
Music has been and always will be a big part of my life. It is one of the things that truly crosses party lines and humanizes all of us. Thank you The New York Times for sharing my love of music!

Hope everyone in Eaton, Ingham and Clinton counties stay safe over the weekend as Consumers Energy works to repair the damage from the storm. If you come across a downed power line, please call 911 or Consumers Energy at 1-800-477-5050.

FOX 2 Detroit reporter, Ron Savage, dedicated his life to his community. It’s great to see that he and his legacy will be honored this weekend at the Savage Days – Ribs on the River cookout in Milford.
Happy 130th anniversary to the historic Grand Hotel! For generations, you have given us irreplaceable memories and today you continue to be a beautiful gem in our state.
Sending my deepest condolences to the friends and loved ones of former Detroit News and WDIV Local 4 / ClickOnDetroit journalist, Bob Pisor, during this hard time.

Congress is back in session this week and Republicans are still trying to pass their terrible health care bill. Felicia Parris, William Dennis, Abba Jones and Darin Phillips are just some of the countless people in Michigan that will be hurt by Trumpcare. We need you to keep sharing stories about ways Trumpcare would hurt you or your family! #AmericaSpeaksOut.
My prayers and deepest condolences go out to the loved ones of Julian Kevianne from Detroit and the 15 other U.S. Marine Corps heroes who died in the plane crash in Mississippi yesterday.
Warmest congratulations to Crystal Smith from Detroit on winning Food Network's Chopped! Michigan is proud of you and excited to see what you do next.
NA

Families who have loved ones struggling with opioid abuse know how addiction can shatter lives. We need to focus on more treatment options to stop this devastating and costly epidemic.  You can count on my continued commitment to secure critical funding for services and additional resources for families

I am so thankful to all the doctors, nurses and advocates who have come from Michigan and from all across the country to D.C. in an effort to speak out against the Republican health care bill. I want to especially thank Dr. Meigs, President of American Academy of Family Physicians (AAFP) for joining me in our interview with Kasie Hunt on MSNBC
The Proton Therapy Center at Beaumont Health is the first of its kind in Michigan.  Great innovation in the fight against cancer!

The Republican health care bill is still a bad deal for Michigan. Doctors, nurses, hospitals and insurance companies all know that this is a bad bill. We should be working together in order to stabilize the marketplace, reduce out-of-pocket costs and lower the outrageous costs of prescription drugs for our families in Michigan.
Our state holds so much beauty. The latest northern lights show over the Mackinac Bridge gave breathtaking views!
Congratulations to the 19 Crain's Detroit Business Health Care Heroes winners. Michigan is truly proud of your dedication, achievements and contributions to our communities.
Great to welcome Shelly and Laura from Milton Manufacturing, a terrific women owned business #MadeInDetroit
Congratulations to Rod Kallgren, from Dearborn, on achieving his goal of eight holes-in-one in honor of his sons, wife and even himself. What a great story!
Great to talk to Bustle about health care and what it's like to serve in the Senate. Watch our interview here!

We take a lot of pride in our craft beer in Michigan! The MI Brewers Guild 20th Annual Summer Beer Festival this weekend is the perfect chance to celebrate years of great milestones in this industry, including contributing more than $600 million to our economy.
What an exciting chance to own part of Michigan State Basketball history. Glad to see pieces of the Breslin Student Events Center finding good Spartan homes!

The new women’s business lounge in the Detroit community is truly an inspiring place to grow ideas and support the entrepreneurial dreams of Michigan women! Great job, Meagan Ward from Creatively Flawless!

Congrats to Mike Conrad from Royal Oak High School on being one of only 30 teachers selected to participate in C-SPAN educators’ conference. Michigan is proud of you and your dedication to your students!
Senator Gary Peters and I have requested a meeting with Trump to discuss supporting our Michigan manufacturers. Let’s work together to end outsourcing and implement strong Buy American laws!
About to join U.S. Senate Democrats to #ProtectOurCare. Tune in!
NA

It’s deeply disturbing that Republicans voted today to begin consideration of their bill to repeal the health care law.  I spoke on the Capitol steps on behalf of Michigan families who will be hurt by the Trumpcare bill, which gives tax breaks to drug companies while stripping health care coverage from millions in Michigan.  Watch here:

My colleague, Senator Ron Wyden, is right; bipartisanship is how the Senate works best. We should be working together to address the real problems with this bill – like the high cost of copays, premiums and prescription drugs.
So great to meet JDRF Type 1 diabetes advocates during Children's Congress today! Thanks for coming to the Hill to testify!
Sending heartfelt condolences to friends, former colleagues and loved ones of Martin Buth, who spent his entire life contributing to our West Michigan community.

Proud to see Ann Arbor, Michigan being recognized as the most educated city in the U.S. and Lansing, Michigan as No. 14! These are just two of our wonderful cities accomplishing so many great things in Michigan!
The latest Republican health care plan is the same bad news - it drives up costs for Michigan families and makes sure fewer people have insurance!
This is a great concept for a mural and is the perfect addition to Muskegon’s Nelson Neighborhood. Great job to the kids from the Youth Empowerment Project who developed the idea!

Incredible to see the evolution of the Ford Motor Company Model TT truck since its introduction 100 years ago today. Its innovation had a significant impact on our agriculture and manufacturing industries in Michigan.
NA

It's past 9pm and we still haven't seen the text of the health care bill Republicans want to vote on tonight! For Republicans, this is a political exercise, but for Michigan families, it's personal. There is nothing more personal than getting nursing home care or cancer care. People in Michigan deserve to know what is in this bill. Watch my remarks tonight on the Senate Floor:

Over the past few months, so many people in Michigan and across the country shared their stories, made phone calls and spoke out against the Republican health care bill. Because of these actions, the attempts to take away health care from millions of Americans failed last night. It's now important that we work on a bipartisan basis to find solutions that lower health care costs and improve care.

I was so honored to meet with Specialist Jim McCloughan in my office today.  On Monday, he will receive the Medal of Honor to commend his heroic service in Vietnam.  I am honored to have been able to play a  role in ensuring Jim finally gets the recognition he deserves.  Read more here: https://www.stabenow.senate.gov/news/ahead-of-white-house-medal-of-honor-ceremony-stabenow-peters-upton-congratulate-vietnam-veteran-james-mccloughan-on-receiving-our-nations-highest-military-honor
The Qline continues to be a great way to connect Detroiters through its 12 locations on Woodward from the North End through downtown. Glad to see the ridership exceeding expectations!
Happy 150th Anniversary to the city of Montague! Be sure to check out this great list of events to celebrate one of our truly historic cities in Michigan!
Last weekend, I continued my small business tour in Coldwater and had the chance to stop by the wonderful Bell's Eccentric Café in Kalamazoo!
I had the opportunity to visit Golden Shoes during my small business tour in Traverse City. Warmest congratulations on being recognized as a finalist for America’s Retail Champion of the Year!

This partnership is an exciting opportunity for Michigan workers to get the skills training needed for a good-paying job in our tech industry. I am glad to see both Detroit and Grand Rapids being able to participate!
Many people don’t realize all the beautiful scenery and exciting activities Michigan has to offer, especially in the Upper Peninsula. This piece provides a great glimpse!
What an honor to see Jim "Doc" McCloughan receive the Medal of Honor. We all thank this American hero for his service!

It was an absolute honor to witness Specialist James McCloughan receive one of the nation’s highest and most prestigious awards. The Medal of Honor could not have gone to a more deserving recipient. Thank you, Jim, for your bravery and exemplary service to our country.
Warmest congratulations to Miss Michigan’s Outstanding Teen, Katie Preston from Bridgman, on finishing in the top 5 of the Miss America's Outstanding Teen Pageant!

For over 60 years, Dr. John Dorsey has shown remarkable dedication to his profession and community. From serving in the Navy to inspiring his patients and colleagues, he truly has made Michigan proud.
The Poe Lock is the only lock most ships can travel through, making it critical to our economy and national security. This upgrade is important until we can construct another Poe-sized lock.
I’m so glad I had the opportunity to be a part of the Grand Haven Coast Guard festival over the weekend. What a great way to continue the celebration of our U.S. Coast Guard!
Joining Senator Joe Donnelly Senator Tammy Baldwin U.S. Senator Bob Casey U.S. Senate Democrats to introduce our A Better Deal on Trade and Jobs. Watch here:

We need fair trade policies that create good-paying Michigan jobs. We need to pass my Bring Jobs Home Act to close tax loopholes that encourage jobs being shipped overseas.  And we need strong Buy American laws - NOW!
This crucial funding secured in last year’s Flint agreement will help health providers monitor the health of children and adults who were exposed to lead in Flint.

Excited to see that our Chapel Rock from Pictured Rocks National Lakeshore will be No. 41 in the America the Beautiful Quarters Program. Now people all across America can keep a small part of Michigan beauty in their pockets.

We believe in an America where people who work hard every day should know someone has their back. Whether you're working in a factory, a small business or on a farm, you deserve to have the confidence in knowing that our country and our laws work for you.
This is a very important part of our help for Flint families - making sure their long term health and education needs are addressed. ABC12: Your Trusted Source! WJRT-TV
For those of us that enjoy hops, there is no shortage of places to go in Michigan for National IPA Day! Here are some great recommendations via MLive.com
The Grand Rapids Press: Another hidden gem in the UP; the Canyon Falls and Gorge is filled with beautiful trails and scenic views of the river.
With City of Wayne-Administration and NOAA Great Lakes Environmental Research Laboratory celebrating the successful Wayne Road Dam Removal project!

People between the ages of 55 and 64 often have more health problems and face higher health care costs but aren’t yet eligible for Medicare.  My bill would let you buy into Medicare before you turn 65!  Read more about it here:

Every day is a Pure Michigan day in Wayne!   Great to stop by the Rouge River on Friday to talk about the federal investment we’ve made to protect our lakes and rivers.  The Great Lakes Restoration Initiative supports our state’s economy and helps families enjoy fishing, hunting, boating, and our Michigan way of life.
Highlighting another Great Lakes Restoration Initiative success story on the Kalamazoo River with Kalamazoo Nature Center and Arcadia Ales!
It’s encouraging that the Army Corps is considering concrete actions to stop Asian carp from entering our Great Lakes.  We need to move as quickly as possible to get permanent solutions in place!
Alzheimer's is a heartbreaking disease that impacts individuals and their families. Thank you, Toby, for your activism!  Together, we're all fighting to #EndAlzheimers.

I have visited over 100 small businesses across Michigan and each visit continues to inspire me as I see owners investing their own time and resources into making their communities more successful. I look forward to continuing my tour and meeting with those that truly are the backbone of our economy.

This August, I’m traveling across Michigan to highlight the projects that make our Great Lakes Restoration Initiative a success. The Kalamazoo Nature Center is the perfect example of why we need to stop any proposal to eliminate crucial funding that protects our Michigan way of life. Fox-17 WXMI
Sending wishes for an incredible birthday to my friend and colleague in Congress, Congressman Dan Kildee!

I’ve always said that Michigan is first and foremost a state where we make things and grow things. Whether factories or film studios, breweries or bakeries, I’ll keep fighting to ensure that Michigan entrepreneurs can turn their great ideas into successful businesses. When we help businesses thrive, we help create jobs – and a stronger economy for our entire state. Battle Creek Enquirer

Congratulations to my dear friend, David Hollister, on receiving this special distinction from the City of Lansing. It is my hope that the newly renamed city hall will serve as a lasting testament to your brand of public service to the people of the City of Lansing and the great State of Michigan.

Too many Michigan families and seniors are burdened by high costs that make it harder to get the care they need and pay their bills. We need to do everything we can to crack down on the skyrocketing cost of prescription drugs and increase drug price transparency. WZZM 13 Grand Rapids

President Trump's continued refusal to condemn Nazis and white supremacists for their hate isn't a partisan issue.  It's a moral issue that degrades the core values of our country.  Hate is hate. Period.

We need to face the facts, find consensus and move as quickly as possible on permanent solutions to stop Asian carp. We have the opportunity to be proactive, not reactive. If we work together, I have no doubt we can meet the challenge for our Great Lakes. Detroit News

A modernization to NAFTA is long overdue for Michigan’s economy and these changes must lead to an improvement in our quality of life. The goal must be to export our products, not our jobs! UpNorthLive

This is the first time that a live Silver carp has been found this close to Lake Michigan. Now, we have proof that it went through the Brandon Road Lock and Dam. Time is of the essence to both implement a permanent solution and take immediate steps to stop Asian carp from reaching our Great Lakes.

Had a wonderful time at today's Air Show celebrating Selfridge's first 100 years...here's to 100 more! To our military members, veterans, and families: thank you for a century of service and sacrifice. Our state and nation are indebted to you.
At Selfridge Air National Guard Base celebrating 100 years!
Today, we get to witness a rare opportunity to see a solar eclipse cover Michigan. See specific times for our state here! Detroit Free Press
In Traverse City to highlight the Boardman River restoration project

I was born in Gladwin, raised in Clare and did 4-H in Harrison, so it's always wonderful to be back home with our community and business leaders! I also enjoyed touring Biewer Lumber in McBain. And it was great to sit down with Cadillac manufacturers who continue to create jobs and are leading on critical efforts to expand technical and skilled trades training.

In Traverse City, Michigan shining a light on the Boardman River restoration project that will create more opportunities for families to fish, kayak, and canoe. This work couldn't be done without an amazing team effort here in the community and Great Lakes funding!
Highlighting another Great Lakes success story in Frankenmuth, Michigan on the Cass River!
Thanks to Great Lakes Restoration funding and amazing teamwork, the Rock Ramp fish passage project is another reason for families and anglers to visit Frankenmuth, Michigan
My deepest condolences go to the family and friends of U.S. Navy sailor Kenneth Smith. He is a true hero who dedicated his life to serving and protecting our country.

It’s definitely exciting to see so many high school graduates choosing Michigan State University and so many other great Michigan schools to further their education. Best of luck to all in the new school year!
Thanks to all the Michigan businesses who are stepping up to help those affected by #Harvey!

Today, I kicked off a series of statewide workforce discussions with business and labor leaders as well as parents and educators at the Detroit Electrical Industry Training Center and Mott Community College in Flint.  Not every young person is interested in getting a four-year college degree. It's important that they know there are great jobs in professional skilled trades and technical careers. We all need to work together to raise public awareness of these great job opportunities across Michigan. Thank you to all the folks who are already working hard to get the word out. I'll be introducing legislation on workforce development in the fall. Stay tuned for more!

It's important that young people in Michigan know they can get a great job in the skilled trades. Talked to WDIV Local 4 / ClickOnDetroit yesterday about my conversations with business and labor leaders in Warren as well as parents and educators!

I continued my series of statewide workforce discussions today at the Michigan Laborers' Training and Apprenticeship Institute in Perry and Kent ISD in Grand Rapids. Had great conversations with business and labor leaders as well as educators and some awesome students and parents on ways we can work together to close the skills gap!
Not every young person is interested in getting a four-year college degree. They should know there are a lot of great jobs in professional skilled trades and technical careers. MLive.com
Important new effort from Michigan Manufacturers Association! Great opportunity for students to learn and develop important skills.
Eid Al-Adha Mubarak to all our Muslim friends. Sending thoughts of happiness and love on your holiday!
Wishing @MSUathletics the best of luck as they kick off their season today against the Bowling Green Falcons. Go Green!
Great to be with so many Michigan working men and women who have joined a union to fight every day for good paying jobs. Thanks for creating our middle class!

Skilled trades training is both a great opportunity for people and an urgent need for businesses in Michigan. In order for our economy to grow, we must provide the tools needed for career and technical education. 9&10 News
Glad Battle Creek opened its doors to a family from #Houston who fled #Harvey.  Michigan welcomes you! Battle Creek Enquirer

This morning, I’m speaking in the Senate Finance Commitee about the need to extend critical funding for the Children’s Health Insurance Program before it expires at the end of the month.    I’m going to share the story of one of my constituents, Jan, whose daughter Suzi benefitted from CHIP.  Suzi was diagnosed with ADHD and bipolar disorder as a young adult.  Thanks to MIChild, her family was able to afford the medical care she needed to be successful.    We need to make sure families like Suzi and Jan’s can continue to rely on CHIP by extending funding for another five years!
The Children’s Health Insurance Program has a long history of bipartisan support, because we all agree that children must have access to the health care they need.

As part of my small business tour, I recently met with RAMI, a small manufacturer of high-tech military products in #Michigan.  Their CEO told me that our #BuyAmerica provisions aren’t working.  We checked into it and they were absolutely right! Over the past five years, the Department of Defense spent $35 billion on over 150,000 products that didn’t meet #BuyAmerica rules!  Those products – motorcycles, radios, even jet engines – could have been made by Michigan workers and manufacturers like RAMI!  American taxpayer dollars should be used to buy products made in America, not overseas.  That’s why I introduced three amendments to the #NDAA that will strengthen #BuyAmerica requirements.  Read more here:   https://www.stabenow.senate.gov/news/stabenow-introduces-amendments-to-national-defense-authorization-act-to-strengthen-buy-american-requirements

My statement on last night’s vote on the Republican tax bill in the Senate Finance Committee:   “There’s no question that we need tax reform that makes the tax system simpler, puts more money in your pocket, closes tax loopholes that send jobs overseas and supports small businesses and farms.  Unfortunately, the Senate bill does not achieve these important goals.    “I voted no because I could not support raising taxes on middle income taxpayers and leaving Michigan families without health insurance to pay for huge tax giveaways for the wealthiest one percent of Americans.  “This was a missed opportunity to work together in a bipartisan way on real tax reform.  I remain committed to passing tax reform that helps middle-class families, small businesses, farmers, and manufacturers.”

My statement on tonight's Senate vote on the Republican tax bill:   “I’ve said from the beginning that we need tax reform that makes the tax system simpler, puts more money in your pocket, closes tax loopholes that send jobs overseas and supports small businesses and farms across Michigan. Unfortunately, that isn’t at all what this Republican bill does.    “I voted no because I could not support raising taxes on middle-class families, seniors, and farmers and leaving Michigan families without health insurance to pay for huge tax giveaways for the wealthiest one percent of Americans.   “This was a lost opportunity to work together in a bipartisan way on real tax reform. My statement following this morning's vote on the Republican tax bill conference report:   “We need tax reform that puts more money in the pockets of the middle class, closes tax loopholes that send jobs overseas and supports small businesses and farms across Michigan—unfortunately, this bill does none on these things. This bill actually raises taxes on middle-class families and seniors and leaves Michigan families without health insurance to pay for huge tax giveaways for the wealthiest one percent of Americans. This was a missed opportunity to work together in a bipartisan way on real tax reform.”
